  "body": "\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe internal csi driver called NodePublish without probing the external driver.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nPrior to calling NodePublish RPC, Kubernetes must probe the external driver for readiness.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nDeploy a pod that uses a csi-backed volume.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
